{"lines":[{"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"2. تَحْتَ \"under\". The noun following تَحْتَ is in the genitive case because it is mudaf ilaihi: تَحْتَ المَكْتَبِ، تَحْتَ الكِتَابِ"}]},{"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"3. يَا is a vocative particle. A noun following يَا has only one dammah: يَا أُسْتَاذُ، يَا شَيْخُ، يَا بِلآلُ not  يَا بِلآلٌ etc."}]},{"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"4. The words اِسْمٌ and اِبْنٌ commence with hamzatu l-wasl. When preceded by a word the initial <<i>> is dropped in pronunciation."}]},{"mode":"card","lines":[{"tap":0,"words":[{"w":"اِسْمُ  الْوَلَدِ  بِلآلٌ","sp":[8,11]}]},{"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"ism-u l-walad-i bilal-u-n"}]},{"tap":0,"words":[{"w":"وَاسْمُ  الْبِنْتِ  آمِنَةُ ","sp":[0,2,9,12]}]},{"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"wa sm-u l-bint-i aminat-u"}]},{"tap":0,"words":[{"w":"اِبْنُ الْمُدَرِّسِ طَبِيْبٌ ","sp":[7,10]}]},{"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"ibn-u l-mudarris-i tabib-u-n"}]},{"tap":0,"words":[{"w":"وَابْنُ  الإِمَمِ  يَاجِرٌ ","sp":[0,2,9,11]}]},{"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"wa bn-u l-imam-i tajir-u-n"}]},{"tap":0,"words":[{"w":"أَيْنَ  ابْنُ  حَامِدٍ "}]},{"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"aina bn-u hamid-i-n?"}]}]},{"d":"ltr","mode":"lesson","height":50,"words":[{"w":"Vocabulary:"}]},{"mode":"vocab","words":[{"w":"الرَّسُولُ","e":"messenger"},{"w":"تَحْتَ","e":"under, beneath"},{"w":"العَمُّ","e":"paternal uncle"},{"w":"الاِبْنُ","e":"son"},{"w":"الشَّرِعُ","e":"street"},{"w":"السَّيَّارَةُ","e":"car"},{"w":"الكَعْبَةُ","e":"Kaabah"},{"w":"هُنَا","e":"here"},{"w":"الخَالُ","e":"maternal uncle"},{"w":"هُنَاكَ","e":"there"},{"w":"مُغْلَقٌ","e":"closed, shut"},{"w":"البِنْتُ","e":"daughter, girl"},{"w":"الاِسْمُ","e":"name"},{"w":"الحَقِيبَةُ","e":"bag, case"}]}]}